# Hacker News usernames for the "My Reading" section.
#
# HOW TO USE
# ----------
# The recommended approach is to set HN_USERNAME as a GitHub Actions
# repository Variable (repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Variables).
# That way your username is never committed to source control, so forks of
# this blog start with a clean slate — they won't display your HN activity.
#
# For local development only, you may create the file
#   config/hackernews.txt
# (without the .example extension) and add one username per line.
# That filename is gitignored, so it will never be committed.
#
# The ingestor fetches your story submissions and comments via the
# Algolia HN Search API (https://hn.algolia.com/api/v1) — no API key needed.
#
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES (remove the leading # to activate)
# ----------------------------------------------------
# HanClinto
